FBIS4-43600 "drweu118_p_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 GREECE Government Wants Clarification on McCurry Statement Government Wants Clarification on McCurry Statement NC1706121894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1130 GMT 17 Jun 94 NC1706121894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said that following yesterday's double demarches on U.S. State Department Spokesman Michael McCurry's statement, the Greek Government would receive with satisfaction any clarification from the U.S. side. He added that McCurry's position, on setting the airspace and territorial waters at six miles, basically concerns NATO's maneuvers and is related to the more general, international U.S. positions.
